      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HONG KONG PHOOEY (4) jumped favourite and was too quick with an all-the-way win last start (22.58) at this track in a Grade 4/5 over 400m. Winner at her latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Shapes as a top winning chance on latest effort. XENI BALE (1) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by half a length at this track in a handy 22.71 beating Time Has Come. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. HUDSON (2) ran below best last time finishing seventh (23.13) over 400m at this track from Box 2. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Should be about the mark. BERN WEST BOLTER (7) hit the frame latest (22.54) when second at this track in a Grade 4. Has already won out of this draw.",
